TASK 1: LANGUAGE TRANSLATION TOOL
Objective
To design a simple language translation tool that allows users to enter text, choose source and target languages, translate the text using a translation API, and display the translated output. Optional features like copy and text-to-speech improve usability.
________________________________________
1. User Interface Design
The user interface includes:
•	A text area for user input
•	Dropdown menus to select source and target languages
•	A translate button
•	An output area to display translated text
•	Optional buttons for copy and text-to-speech
HTML Code
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>Language Translation Tool</title>
</head>
<body>

<h2>Language Translation Tool</h2>

<textarea id="inputText" placeholder="Enter text"></textarea><br><br>

<select id="sourceLang">
  <option value="en">English</option>
  <option value="fr">French</option>
  <option value="es">Spanish</option>
</select>

<select id="targetLang">
  <option value="fr">French</option>
  <option value="en">English</option>
  <option value="es">Spanish</option>
</select>

<br><br>
<button onclick="translateText()">Translate</button>

<br><br>
<textarea id="outputText" placeholder="Translated text" readonly></textarea>

<br><br>
<button onclick="copyText()">Copy</button>
<button onclick="speakText()">Text to Speech</button>

<script src="script.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
________________________________________
2. Translation API Integration
The tool uses Microsoft Translator API to process translations. The text is sent via a POST request, and the translated response is received in JSON format.
JavaScript Code
async function translateText() {
  const text = document.getElementById("inputText").value;
  const from = document.getElementById("sourceLang").value;
  const to = document.getElementById("targetLang").value;

  const response = await fetch(
    "https://api.cognitive.microsofttranslator.com/translate?api-version=3.0&from="
    + from + "&to=" + to,
    {
      method: "POST",
      headers: {
        "Ocp-Apim-Subscription-Key": "YOUR_API_KEY",
        "Ocp-Apim-Subscription-Region": "YOUR_REGION",
        "Content-Type": "application/json"
      },
      body: JSON.stringify([{ text: text }])
    }
  );

  const data = await response.json();
  document.getElementById("outputText").value =
    data[0].translations[0].text;
}
________________________________________
3. Optional Features
Copy Translated Text
function copyText() {
  const output = document.getElementById("outputText");
  output.select();
  document.execCommand("copy");
  alert("Text copied!");
}
Text-to-Speech
function speakText() {
  const text = document.getElementById("outputText").value;
  const speech = new SpeechSynthesisUtterance(text);
  window.speechSynthesis.speak(speech);
}
________________________________________
4. Output
•	The translated text is displayed clearly in the output text area.
•	Users can copy the translation or listen to it using text-to-speech.
________________________________________
5. Conclusion
This task successfully demonstrates the implementation of a language translation tool using a translation API. The application provides an intuitive interface, accurate translations, and enhanced usability through additional features like copy and speech functionality.
